#text": "the term ", "external-xref": {"#tail": " of title 47, Code of Federal Regulations);", "@parsable-cite": "cfr/47/54.5", "#text": "section 54.5", "@legal-doc": "regulation"}, "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity": {"#tail": ") that is a rate-of-return carrier (as defined in ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " (", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 153 of the Communications Act of 1934", "@value": "Communications Act of 1934/s:153"}, "@entity-type": "law-citation", "#text": "\n            ", "external-xref": {"#tail": ")", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "\n          ", "@entity-type": "uscode", "#text": "47 U.S.C. 153", "@value": "usc/47/153"}, "@parsable-cite": "usc/47/153", "#text": "\n            ", "@legal-doc": "usc"}}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(5)"}, "@id": "id68aed4489184424984612bd694bae6f1", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "term": {"#tail": " means the cost calculated under ", "#text": "study area total unseparated loop cost"}, "#text": "the term ", "external-xref": {"#tail": " of title 47, Code of Federal Regulations;", "@parsable-cite": "cfr/47/36.621", "#text": "section 36.621", "@legal-doc": "regulation"}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(6)"}, "@id": "id7338c16823924a6cbaa6daba3fc57fcb", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " adopted on October 27, 2011 (FCC 11\u2013161); and", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Federal Communications Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}, "term": {"#tail": " means the Report and Order and Further Notice of Proposed Rulemaking of the ", "#text": "Transformation Order"}, "#text": "the term "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(7)"}, "@id": "id22c311f40ec94faca36d46b3accaa0b1", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "term": {"#tail": " has the meaning given the term in ", "#text": "tribal lands"}, "#text": "the term ", "external-xref": {"#tail": " of title 47, Code of Federal Regulations.", "@parsable-cite": "cfr/47/54.400", "#text": "section 54.400(e)", "@legal-doc": "regulation"}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(8)"}, "@id": "ida55b5d573fff460c95927f51d91daf2e", "#text": "\n        "}], "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "id137cae7bae354207995ced4f66497d45"}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " finds the following:", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Congress", "@entity-id": "0001"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@display-inline": "no-display-inline"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "3."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "Findings"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "The implementation of new rules and regulations set forth in the Transformation Order has created financial uncertainty and instability for rural carriers by denying rural carriers a meaningful opportunity to recover investments and expenses incurred to provide universal service prior to 2012."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(1)"}, "@id": "idf6b5df91d35b4aeaaff87f49ec64f14c", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "The implementation of the Transformation Order, including the utilization of a widely criticized regression analysis used to determine levels of universal service support, is creating significant uncertainty with respect to the sufficiency and predictability of the universal service support mechanisms, which has discouraged rural carriers from making broadband infrastructure investments to build out new broadband capabilities in high cost-to-serve rural communities throughout the United States."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(2)"}, "@id": "id1c501d66385340c0997c67bb34729915", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " under ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Congress", "@entity-id": "0001"}, {"#tail": "\u2014", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}], "#text": "The intent of ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity": {"#tail": " is that the ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " (", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 254 of the Communications Act of 1934", "@value": "Communications Act of 1934/s:254"}, "@entity-type": "law-citation", "#text": "\n            ", "external-xref": {"#tail": ")", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "\n          ", "@entity-type": "uscode", "#text": "47 U.S.C. 254", "@value": "usc/47/254"}, "@parsable-cite": "usc/47/254", "#text": "\n            ", "@legal-doc": "usc"}}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(3)"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "id34cb36e5f6d34781bd33fa0c509ce838", "subparagraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "  before adopting changes to regulations that affect universal service high-cost fund mechanisms; and", "@entity-parent-id": "2700", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Federal-State Joint Board on Universal Service", "@value": "Federal-State Joint Board on Universal Service"}, "#text": "consult with the "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(A)"}, "@id": "idad0f1a62821c48aea67b1c9f0dcb6e0c", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "quote": {"#tail": " support mechanisms to preserve and advance universal service.", "#text": "specific, predictable, and sufficient"}, "#text": "adopt policies and regulations that establish and maintain "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(B)"}, "@id": "idfa27d4e2850449b6b7cf7c0526d75859", "#text": "\n          "}]}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " has warned that the implementation of the Transformation Order is having unintended consequences for rural broadband investment and deployment and for other Federal programs designed to promote rural broad\u00adband deployment.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary of Agriculture", "@entity-id": "1200"}, "#text": "The "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(4)"}, "@id": "id9f42849dda764a2382a668f26250f9d0", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " has reported that demand for ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Department of Agriculture", "@entity-id": "1200"}, {"#tail": " loans for broadband buildout has plummeted in 2013, due in part to the uncertainty created by the new rules and regulations set forth in the Transformation Order.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Rural Utilities Service", "@entity-id": "12E2"}], "#text": "The "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(5)"}, "@id": "id9da9e079ff1e4337b0decfda0d89b5a1", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "Surveys of rural carriers indicate that nearly two-thirds of rural rate-of-return carriers are canceling or postponing new broadband investments, while other reports indicate that rural rate-of-return carriers are being forced to increase consumer prices and reduce staff, creating ripple effects for economies in rural areas of the United States."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(6)"}, "@id": "idad021e6ac3374603bf9ff3b9375f121c", "#text": "\n        "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " to the consideration, review, and resolution of petitions for waivers from rules adopted under the Transformation Order\u2014", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}, "#text": "Congressional hearings have demonstrated that the approach of the "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(7)"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "id891a1445f361477eaf54a06eca839329", "subparagraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "; and", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}, "#text": "is unduly burdensome and costly for small, rural carriers and inconsistent with the established policy and waiver standards of the "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(A)"}, "@id": "id0e487227e11f4b36bc0fe1bb3fa8dd0d", "#text": "\n          "}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "is consequently discouraging small, rural carriers from requesting waivers and is creating additional business uncertainties."}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n          ", "#text": "(B)"}, "@id": "idb6365331020445959fd0325bac821163", "#text": "\n          "}]}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " can make adjustments to the Transformation Order to address the adverse impact and business uncertainties confronting small, rural carriers without affecting other categories of carriers or increasing the Universal Service Fund budget established in the Transformation Order.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}, "#text": "Congressional hearings have demonstrated that the "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(8)"}, "@id": "id47f71699cf1b4d87bcba4bc365af478c", "#text": "\n        "}], "#text": "\n      ", "@id": "id77c99255eeea47e8af15c31ad59c098b"}, {"#tail": "\n    ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "4."}, "header": {"#tail": "\n      ", "#text": "Suspension and revision of provision of Transformation Order"}, "subsection": [{"#tail": "\n      ", "text": {"#tail": "\n      ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": "), shall have no force or effect.", "@entity-parent-id": "2700", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Wireline Competition Bureau", "@value": "Wireline Competition Bureau"}, "#text": "\n          ", "external-xref": {"#tail": " of title 47, Code of Federal Regulations (relating to the annual limitation of study area total unseparated loop cost pursuant to a schedule announced by the ", "@parsable-cite": "cfr/47/36.621", "#text": "Section 36.621(a)(5)", "@legal-doc": "regulation"}}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(a)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Suspension"}, "#text": "\n        ", "@id": "id4aa422ceef0f43548e008d9c5be4d19b"}, {"#tail": "\n      ", "enum": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "(b)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n        ", "#text": "Review and revision"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n        ", "subparagraph": [{"#tail": "\n          ", "text": {"#tail": "\n          ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": " shall issue a notice of proposed rulemaking to adopt a revised proposal for rural support.", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}, "#text": "Not later than 60 days after the effective date of this Act, the "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n            ", "#text": "(A)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n            ", "#text": "Requirement to submit proposal"}, "#text": "\n            ", "@id": "id20b8e31524ce43fcaf691cf85779e6ce"}, {"#tail": "\n          ", "text": {"#tail": "\n          ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": " shall ensure that the revised proposal for rural support does not deprive a rural rate-of-return carrier of the opportunity to recover reasonable investments and operating expenses incurred prior to the adoption under ", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Commission", "@entity-id": "2700"}, {"#tail": " of the revised proposal for rural support.